         <abstract>
            <p>9/10 of federal, and 3/4 of state, tax collections, are derived from the same source. That is why federal taxes concern the states. Unless the orbits of governmental activity are greatly diminished, federal, state, and local impositions will remain inextricably entwined. Up to now, little has been done toward coordination. A Federal-State Fiscal Authority could do much towards coordination, if it could function effectively. Exploration of coordinating methods must be continued.</p>
         </abstract>
